==English==

==={{abbreviation}}=== See note below from Wikipedia article on ISO.
'''ISO'''
# [[w:International Organization for Standardization|International Organization for Standardization]]
# {{computing}}: A typical file extention for an image of a [[CD]] or [[DVD]].



== Note ==

The organization is usually referred to simply as ISO (pronounced eye-so). It is a common misconception that ISO stands for "International Standards Organization", or something similar. ISO is not an acronym; it comes from the Greek word isos, meaning "equal".

